        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 25 at 10:38AM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 1038 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles southeast of Concord, or 14 miles east of Heber Springs, moving
east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Oil Trough...                     Hickory Flat...
Thida...                          Salado...
Bradford...                       Dewey...
Heffington...                     Fitzhugh...
Huff...                           Pleasant Plains...
Velvet Ridge...                   Steprock...
Roosevelt...                      Olyphant...
Clay...                           Ingleside...
Rosie...                          Southside in Independence Count...
Jacksonport...                    Magness...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
